About the

platform

The platform will provide the Urban teams with a centralised, spatially intelligent interface that brings together key datasets, analytical tools, KPIs, and reference materials.


This tool will enable review and scenario planning to guide strategic estate management and investment decisions, and support the implementation of the Playbook's Place Ambition.
Transforming the West End

About the Proof of Concept

Prior + Partners have developed a proof of concept version of the platform to illustrate its potential and functionality. The platform will include intuitive web applications and dashboards focused on the phasing of development projects across the estate and a sector-based analysis of commercial floorspace.

Transforming the

West End

A web-based geospatial dashboard presenting developments across the estate in an intuitive, time-sequenced 3D environment.


It communicates the phasing of the estate, including development pipeline, capital works, public realm and key infrastructure projects to support strategic planning and decision-making.
Scroll to dashboard
Key features

01 A 3D representation of the development pipeline and capital works programme showing phasing timelines and project sequencing;


02 Visualisation of the Future of RSHPC public realm and district energy network layers showing phasing timelines to provide spatial context and support integrated decision-making;


03 Filtering and navigation tools to allow users to explore projects by time frame, type, or location.


04 Compare properties to identify strategic opportunities and minimise risk.

Commercial Floorspace

A web-based geospatial dashboard that maps commercial floor space across the estate in an intuitive 3D, time-aware environment. It gives decision-makers a clear view of current and future occupancy, highlighting where to grow, reshape, or accelerate the commercial pipeline.
Scroll to dashboard
Key features

01 A 3D representation of the commercial floor space showing tenancy timelines and current occupation status to support integrated decision-making;



02 Filtering and navigation tools to allow users to explore projects by time frame, type, or location.
